{
  "text": "Balanite aegyptiaca is an evergreen xerophytic tree (known as desert date) of huge medicinal importance in Sudanese traditional medical practice. It belongs to the family Balanitaceae, native to Africa, parts of Middle East as well as drier parts of India [CITATION_1] Found in many kinds of habitat and different types of soils in Sudan, it is well-distributed from northern Saharan region across to the southern Savannah.",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "199606109"
